import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Load US states shapefile
    us_states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json")

    # Count airports per state
    airport_counts = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='count')

    # Merge airport counts with states shapefile
    us_states = us_states.merge(airport_counts, left_on='name', right_on='state')

    # Create choropleth map
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 25))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    us_states.plot(column='count', ax=ax, legend=True, cax=cax, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)

    # Set title and legend
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports across different states in the US?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_axis_off()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Assuming the dataset contains a column 'num_flights' representing the number of flights handled by each airport
    data['num_flights'].plot.hist(bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airport sizes based on the number of flights they handle?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Number of Flights")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend(["Airport Sizes"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports based on their location (latitude and longitude)?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group airport names by city
    grouped_data = data.groupby('city')['name'].apply(lambda x: ', '.join(x)).reset_index()

    # Create a text string of airport names separated by commas
    airport_names = ', '.join(grouped_data['name'])

    # Generate a word cloud
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate(airport_names)

    # Plot the word cloud
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airport names across different cities in the US?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopy.distance

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate distance from major cities
    major_cities = {
        'New York': (40.7128, -74.0060),
        'Los Angeles': (34.0522, -118.2437),
        'Chicago': (41.8781, -87.6298),
        'Houston': (29.7604, -95.3698),
        'Phoenix': (33.4484, -112.0740)
    }

    def min_distance(coords):
        return min(geopy.distance.distance(coords, city_coords).km for city_coords in major_cities.values())

    data['distance'] = data.apply(lambda row: min_distance((row['latitude'], row['longitude'])), axis=1)

    # Create heatmap
    heatmap, xedges, yedges = np.histogram2d(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], bins=50)
    extent = [xedges[0], xedges[-1], yedges[0], yedges[-1]]

    plt.imshow(heatmap.T, extent=extent, origin='lower', cmap='viridis')
    plt.colorbar(label='Number of Airports')
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('Distribution of Airport Locations Based on Their Distance from Major Cities', wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
